[thinking] **Considering testing guidelines**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about the issue of keeping coverage for each dynamic-access class in its own dedicated Java test file under src/test/java. It makes sense to maintain that organization for clarity. There's also a concern about not using reflection directly in tests unless the public API requires it. We did use Class.forName and MethodHandles, so that means we accessed an internal package-private class directly. I wonder if that's against best practices?
