[assistant] Fixed the compile failure.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - I had added `protobuf-java` as `testCompileOnly`, which put the full runtime on the compile classpath.
[assistant] - That caused existing tests to resolve `com.google.protobuf.Empty` from `protobuf-java` instead of `protobuf-javalite`, breaking `GeneratedMessageLiteInnerSerializedFormTest`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Fix:
[assistant] - Removed `testCompileOnly "com.google.protobuf:protobuf-java:$libraryVersion"` from:
[assistant]   - `tests/src/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-javalite/3.25.3/build.gradle`
[assistant] - Updated `ExtensionSchemasTest` to avoid compile-time references to full-runtime classes:
[assistant]   - It now loads `com.google.protobuf.DescriptorProtos$MessageOptions` by class name at runtime, using the existing `testRuntimeOnly` dependency.
[assistant] - Added native-image test metadata for that dynamically loaded class:
[assistant]   - `tests/src/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-javalite/3.25.3/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json`
[assistant] 
[assistant] I also validated the edited JSON syntax. Per instruction, I did not run the Gradle test command locally.
[assistant-event] text_end
